From Taka Mizutani Subject Re In article Mika Iisakkila wrote Because of some contract IBM is not allowed to sell its chips to third parties so these chips are unlikely to become available in any non IBM I saw in this months PC or PC World an ad for computers using IBM's So I don't think IBM is restricted in selling their chips at least not A clock tripled even without coprocessor would be great especially with on board Make it pin compatible and you have the chip upgrade that dreams are made of Taka Mizutani